\SE[2]Now let's see.... \!\SE[3]Rebecca has an affinity for
Thunder element, while Lunaroa seems to have an affinity for
Water element.

\SM[double]\SE[3]That's great...! \SE[15]If it's Thunder,
it's so cool, right?! \SE[3]And to think we have the same
affinity as Onee-sama...!

\SE[3]I see. That's convenient because it's easy to teach.
\!\SE[0]I'm not good with the Water element.... Lunaroa, can
you take a look? \!\SE[3]I don't usually see it, but I'm
sure you can use it, right?

\SE[7]Since Lunaroa can use simple magic, it would be good
to have something that can be a little more challenging as a
future goal.

\SE[2]Water element, huh.... Come to think of it, I haven't
really used it much. \SE[13]Um, um, can I practice a
little...?
\SE[21]Oh, I'm glad.... Surprisingly, I remember it....

\SE[2]It seems like Lunaroa is also getting motivated.
\!\SE[2]How can she cast such magic?
\SE[2] How can I...? \SE[0] Hmm... well, that's...

\SE[10]Like this! \SE[11]Now, let's give it a try, Ronoa-
chan!

\SE[22]Like this...! \SE[18]Not like that! Stupid! \SE[22]Is
that how you teach someone...?!?

\SE[52]E-even if you say that, I learned it by doing it like
this...

\SE[75] (That's right. \SE[18] This person, at first glance,
ignores the process and remembers everything... What a
dangerous person.)

\SE[18]Lunaroa.... I've noticed something while watching
you. \SE[19]One of the mysteries that has always puzzled me
has been solved. \SE[66]That is....

\SM[pop]\SE[22]Many geniuses are hopelessly incompetent when
it comes to teaching others!!

\SE[18]Many geniuses often skip the necessary steps and
quickly acquire skills... \SE[19]In other words, they
haven't gone through the usual process that is generally
required, and they fundamentally can't understand the
necessity of it.

\SE[50]However, such geniuses become excellent individuals
and inevitably become people who stand above others....
\SE[51]They end up in a position of teaching others....

\SE[22]And! \.They fully demonstrate their clumsy leadership
skills...! \!\SE[19]The geniuses corrupt the group...!!

\SE[76] It's a sad outcome.... Because of their excellence,
they end up hurting someone.

\SE[19]Enough, go home, Lunaroa. \SE[18]There is nothing you
can do here... There is nothing.

\SE[9]S-So, that's... Even I... \SE[8]I want to be able to
help someone...

\SE[7]Just by being here... \!\SE[23]Am I holding everyone
back...?

\SE[9]P-Please cheer up... Lunaroa-sama...! \SE[13]If you
can show results and prove yourself...! \SE[14]It would be
great if Lunaroa-chan can grow!

\SE[52]That may be true, but... \.Is it okay for me to teach
you...? \!\SE[54]I hope I'm not causing any trouble for you,
Lunaroa-chan...!?

\SE[12]I-I believe in you, Lunaroa-chan...! You're
diligent...! You have talent and sense...!! \SE[13]I trust
her...!!

\SE[13]P-Please look! Lunaroa-sama...!! \SE[1]Isn't it clear
that Ronoa-chan's 'motivation' is contagious...!?

\SE[43]That's right... If I don't get myself together...!
\SE[12]Ronoa-chan...! I will take responsibility and make
you grow...!

\SE[12]Alright...! That's the spirit...! \SE[14]Let's prove
that Lunaroa-sama is not incompetent...! With Ronoa-
chan...!!

\SE[43]That's right...! \!\SE[12]I'm not incompetent.... \.I
will prove it...! \!\SM[nod]\SE[14]With Ronoa-chan...!!
